@startuml domain-control-model
title SafeCrowd Domain Control Model

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

package "domain" {
  package "referenced contracts" {
    class ControlZone {
      zoneId
      name
    }

    class Door {
      doorId
    }

    class Connector {
      connectorId
    }

    class DynamicSource {
      sourceId
    }

    class DynamicObstacleRule {
      ruleId
    }
  }

  class ControlPlan {
    planId
    event sequence
    binding catalog
  }

  class OperationalEvent {
    eventId
    name
    priority
    enabled
  }

  class Trigger {
    triggerId
    evaluation mode
  }

  abstract class TriggerCondition
  class TimeTriggerCondition {
    simulation time
  }
  class StateTriggerCondition {
    metric threshold
    target region
  }

  class OccupantTag {
    tagId
    selection rule
  }

  class Behavior {
    behaviorId
    name
  }

  class BehaviorStep {
    action type
    target selector
    completion rule
  }

  class BehaviorBinding {
    bindingId
    target tag
  }

  class RouteChoiceBinding {
    bindingId
    target tag
  }

  class RouteChoicePolicy {
    policyId
    reroute mode
  }

  class PathCostModel {
    cost weights
  }

  class CostComponent {
    component kind
    weight
  }

  class AccessRuleChange {
    direct target
    access mode
  }

  class ZoneAccessChange {
    zone target
    access mode
  }

  class SourceRateChange {
    source target
    ingress delta
  }

  class DynamicObstacleActivation {
    rule target
    activation mode
  }
}

ControlPlan *-- OperationalEvent
ControlPlan *-- OccupantTag
ControlPlan *-- Behavior
ControlPlan *-- BehaviorBinding
ControlPlan *-- RouteChoiceBinding
ControlPlan ..> ControlZone : controllable groups

OperationalEvent --> Trigger
Trigger *-- TriggerCondition
TriggerCondition <|-- TimeTriggerCondition
TriggerCondition <|-- StateTriggerCondition

Behavior *-- BehaviorStep
BehaviorBinding --> OccupantTag
BehaviorBinding --> Behavior

RouteChoiceBinding --> OccupantTag
RouteChoiceBinding --> RouteChoicePolicy
RouteChoicePolicy --> PathCostModel
PathCostModel *-- CostComponent

OperationalEvent o-- BehaviorBinding : activate / replace
OperationalEvent o-- AccessRuleChange
OperationalEvent o-- ZoneAccessChange
OperationalEvent o-- SourceRateChange
OperationalEvent o-- DynamicObstacleActivation

AccessRuleChange --> Door : target
AccessRuleChange --> Connector : target
ZoneAccessChange --> ControlZone : target
SourceRateChange --> DynamicSource : target
DynamicObstacleActivation --> DynamicObstacleRule : target

note bottom of ControlPlan
  Control is not modeled as raw on/off flags only.
  A plan owns tag bindings, behavior choices,
  route choice bindings, and event sequencing.
end note

note bottom of Trigger
  Initial scope supports time-based and
  state-based trigger conditions.
  More advanced perception or response stages
  can be layered later without renaming events.
end note

note bottom of PathCostModel
  Door choice is expressed as a weighted cost model.
  Typical components are current room travel time,
  queue time, and remaining route cost.
end note

note bottom of OperationalEvent
  Event effects can target direct access points,
  named control zones, dynamic sources,
  and reusable obstacle rules without
  collapsing them into one flag bucket.
end note

@enduml
